Sara Lee in Talks to Buy Brazil Coffee Plant, Valor Reports

-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 
2011-05-18T12:18:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/sara-lee-in-talks-to-buy-brazil-coffee-plant-valor-reports.html
Sara Lee Corp. (SLE)  is in talks to buy a
coffee roasting plant in  Brazil  for 1 billion reais ($619
million) and may use shares to pay for the deal,  Valor Economico 
reported, citing unnamed advisers to the two companies.  The company may buy a plant in Sergipe, Brazil, from  Grupo
Jose Augusto Vieira , Valor said. The plant produces the Marata
coffee brand, tea and fruit-flavored drinks and has sales of 600
million reais annually, the Sao Paulo-based newspaper reported.  Ernesto Duran, a spokesman for Sara Lee, declined to
comment on market rumors. A spokeswoman for Grupo Jose Augusto
Vieira, who can’t be named because of company’s policy, declined
to comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in  Sao Paulo  at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net . 